article.headline: Liberty 88, Anderson, S.C. 46
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. -- Seth Curry scored 22 points and Liberty defeated Anderson, South Carolina 88-46 on Monday night. Curry, who was 4 of 8 from 3-point range, led a strong long-distance shooting night for the Flames (7-2). Liberty was 12 of 22 from 3-point distance and shot 62.1 percent from the field (36 of 58). Curry led four Flames' players in double figures, as Johnny Stephene scored 14, Anthony Smith added 12 and Brolin Floyd chipped in 10. The Trojans (3-4), who shot 30.8 percent from the field (16 of 52) and hit just 6 of 26 of their 3-point shots, didn't have a player score in double figures. Brandon Young was the Trojans' leading scorer with nine points. Young and Nick Trull led Anderson with three field goals each.
